dc_description_s: This data represents nurse aide training programs for Wisconsin in 2024. [This dataset contains locations and attributes of Nurse Aide Training Programs approved by the state of Wisconsin. The data is used for planning, management and analysis by Wisconsin Department of Health Services staff and other government agencies. Nurse Aide Training Programs are training sites/programs/instructors approved by the Division of Quality Assurance (DQA) to train certified nursing assistants (CNAs) that will have the credentials needed to work in DQA-regulated health care facilities such as nursing homes. They can be affiliated with/run by licensed health care facilities or stand-alone programs.For more information, please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/caregiver/nurse-aide/index.htm]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For access to the most current data available, please visit: https://data.dhsgis.wi.gov/datasets/wi-dhs::wisconsin-nurse-aide-training-programs/about
